      • registerArgumentMapperSimple

        public static <T> void registerArgumentMapperSimple(java.lang.Class<T> type,
                                                    java.util.function.Predicate<CommandArgument> isType,
                                                    java.util.function.Function<CommandArgument,T> getAsType)
        This ignores flags. Use registerArgumentMapper(java.lang.Class<T>, com.github.breadmoirai.bot.framework.command.parser.ArgumentTypePredicate, com.github.breadmoirai.bot.framework.command.parser.ArgumentTypeMapper<T>) otherwise.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type
        Parameters:
        type - The type class
        isType - predicate to test if the argument can be parsed to the type provided. This param can be left null if the complexity is close to getAsType.apply(arg) != null
        getAsType - A function to convert the argument to the type provided.

      • getAsType

        public static <T> java.util.Optional<T> getAsType(java.lang.Class<T> type,
                                                  CommandArgument arg,
                                                  int flags)
        Attempts to map the CommandArgument to the type provided using the flags and a registered ArgumentMapper. If an ArgumentMapper is not registered with the type requested, an empty Optional is returned.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type
        Parameters:
        type - the intended type class
        arg - the argument to map from
        flags - any flags
        Returns:
        an Optional containing the result if successful. Otherwise empty.
